5. How does Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) decide when to scale pods?
    HPA monitors metrics such as CPU utilization, memory usage, or custom metrics defined by the user. 
    It compares the current metric values against the target thresholds set in the HPA configuration. 
    If the metrics exceed the target for a specified duration, HPA triggers scaling actions to increase or decrease the number of pods accordingly.

