15. What is a zombie process?
    zombie process is a process that has completed execution but still has an entry in the process table. 
    This occurs when the parent process has not yet read the exit status of the child process, leaving it in a "defunct" state. 
    Zombie processes do not consume CPU or memory resources, but they do occupy a slot in the process table, 
    which can lead to resource exhaustion if many zombies accumulate. 
    To handle zombie processes, the parent process should be designed to properly wait for its child processes to terminate and clean up their exit statuses.
